Bitch...

The smell of rain became thick in the air, and the thunder grew louder.  I thought to myself "I better get home quick, or I'll get wet."

Everyone must feel like this at times.

As I made my return home, and was instantly filled with regret the second I saw my mp3 player hit the pavement.  What did it do to deserve that?  I left it at the scene of the crime, hoping it won't haunt me.

Everyone must feel like this at times.

The second I got home it started pouring.

Everyone must feel like this at times.

I checked my phone to see if I had any messages.  I did.  It was Paul telling me that he loves and misses me.  A smile still lingers on my face.  I feel loved.

Everyone must feel like this at times.

At work I get many complaints from customers that their winter covers are too taut.  This is when I found out no one likes to be called stupid.

Today a little Asian man lived in my head.  He gave me much wisdom.  I think I watched too many episodes of Avatar: The Last Airbender.
Oh God, I'm going to kill myself

The world of Cud....di. What have I been up to? Hmmmm Well I kinda actually like my job at The Great Escape (gaspeth) Like my fellow cashiers a lot =D so at least I'm getting along with people. I'm getting a little better with my chemical knowledge, as well as how to hook up a sand filter if you have a main drain. Go me. Paul and I are doing wonderful, like how we used to do before he dumped me for that dumb girl. I'm madly in love with this guy and sometimes I don't know what to do with myself because of it. I want to be with him constantly, and well usually I am with him constantly. I love him. I kinda miss a few of my friend (ie, blissa, trish, joey, you know who you are) So yeah, ask me to hang out sometime soon, it would be appreciated. Well, if you want to see Paul cuz he'll most likely tag along. I got a new piercing... sort of a modified conch dealy ain't it neat? Later
Serious question this time.  Should I be with Paul?

How would you feel if your family never asked how you were doing.  Never wondered how your day went.  You're gone, everyday, but no one seems to even notice it anymore.  You met a guy, you really like.  He treats you very well, wonders how your day goes.  Calls to ask you how you're feeling.  Hugs you when you're sad.  Smiles with you when you're happy.  You fell in love.  

He dumped you, for four months.

One day he started talking to you again.  You tried your hardest to hate him.  You couldn't.  But you could make him feel bad about the horrible decsision he made.  Time goes on, you start to see him again and realize why you loved him in the first place.  But your family, the ones who NEVER ASK YOU WHAT THE FUCK IS UP, hate him.  Try to get you to dump him.  Ask things like "What possessed you to go back out with him?" or say "He's ugly, you can do better."

Well, people, I ask you this.  How can one do better that see someone who seems to give a fuck about how one feels?

And hey, I think he's goodlooking so fuck off.

Alright, so there are A LOT of people out there, that don't deserve insight to my life. I'm willing to say anyone willing to take the time to read this, deserves to know about me, but lets face the facts. NONE OF YOU PEOPLE READ THIS. I'm stressed out. About everything. It's effecting my mood, my appetite, my sleeping. I constantly have a headache and constantly feel like somethings wrong. Hell, I COULD be crazy. Or I might just have something wrong. I can't stand not having a job. It's killing me, not having money. No way to pay bills, besides having mommy and daddy take care of it. I feel horrible asking my parents who don't have money to take care of my money problems. The stress is getting to me too, I'm acting differently around people I was once at ease with. I'm probably going to fuck up my relationship with Ben, in no time flat. I'm ignoring most of my family. I also see little point in going out on the weekends. The stupidity of all of this is getting to me. I need a job, I need to move out. Living with 7 other people (two of which under the age of 5) is making me go insane! And the fighting... the constant fighting. I can't stand this anymore. I almost wish that my family DID have to move to Florida, and I could just stay here.
What if when you push the red button, nothing happens?

I quit my job, 10 minutes ago.

I'm crying.
G'morning and g'day.  I've been having a good week.  And it will get better.  I'll let ya all know about it later.

Indeed, I'm whiter than sour cream.
